40|$|This {{article is}} devoted to the issues of {{modelling}} and forecasting corporate income tax revenues in Latvia. Procedure of calculation of corporate income <b>tax</b> <b>payments</b> is different as for most taxes, therefore it requires adjustments also to modelling approaches, which are traditionally used for tax revenues forecasting. It is necessary to distinguish between advance payments (usually monthly <b>payments)</b> and final <b>tax</b> <b>payments</b> made in March, April or May. Advance payments depend on previous <b>tax</b> <b>payments</b> adjusted for inflation, but final payments depend on profit. For econometric equations other factors are considered as well. All the analysed methods give similar annual forecasts – between 342. 3 and 359. 2 m EUR. However, it is important, how they are distributed monthly...|$|R
