30|$|The {{traditional}} {{literature on}} the CAPM assumes that investor’s <b>tax</b> <b>payments</b> simply vanish from the model. This assumption {{is not at all}} consistent with the actual behavior of the Treasury. The theory of general equilibrium states that an interest rate rf = 0 will not affect prices if taxes are introduced. We show that this result can be extended to the CAPM if the <b>tax</b> <b>payments</b> are redistributed among investors.|$|R
